Mermaid Class / Module Diagrams (Optional)
Mermaid can also express class‑like relationships:
```mermaid
classDiagram
  class Filter {
    +apply(input: float[]): float[]
    -coeffs: float[]
  }

  class FFT {
    +compute(input: float[]): complex[]
  }

  Filter "1" --&gt; "1" FFT : uses

Rendered:

```{mermaid}
classDiagram
  class Filter {
    +apply(input: float[]): float[]
    -coeffs: float[]
  }

  class FFT {
    +compute(input: float[]): complex[]
  }

  Filter "1" --&gt; "1" FFT : uses
Useful for:

High-level software architecture.
Module relationships in larger ECE software (e.g., drivers, services, UI).


You don’t need to memorize all Mermaid diagram types; focus on flowcharts and sequence diagrams first.
Just know that it can scale to more formal UML-like diagrams if needed.
